<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1931-08-10T16:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1931-08-10T16:00:00-05:00" n="136" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d136">
                                <note rend="inline" type="source">462.00R296/4905: Telegram</note>
                                <head><hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Great Britain</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Atherton</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Acting Secretary of
                                            State</gloss></hi></head>
                                <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Extract]</seg></opener>
                                <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">London</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1931-08-10T22:00:00+01:00">August 10, 1931—10
                                            p.m.</date><lb/>[Received August 10—7:55
                                        p.m.]</dateline></opener>
                                <p>330. From Livesey. Belgium has annexed its German Mark Agreement
                                    to the committee report by the following footnote to paragraph
                                    2: <quote rend="blockquote">
                                        <p>“The Belgian Government while willingly agreeing to
                                            President Hoover’s proposal was obliged to reserve the
                                            question of the payments to be made by Germany in
                                            fulfillment of the Marks Agreement dated July 13, 1929.
                                            An agreement has been arrived at on this point between
                                            the two Governments which has been embodied in an
                                            exchange of letters herewith annexed.”<note n="77" xml:id="d136fn77">See paragraph No. 9 of the final
                                                report of the International Committee of Experts,
                                                Great Britain, Cmd. 3947, Misc. No. 19 (1931), p.
                                                5.</note></p>
                                    </quote></p>
                                <p rend="center">. . . . . . . . . . . . . .</p>
                                <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Atherton</hi></signed></closer>
                            </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>